<emphasis bold="true" box="[98,232,927,960]" pageId="36" pageNumber="588">Breeding.</emphasis>
There is no information available for this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="588" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="36.[95,1305,302,1317]" pageId="36" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[96,335,967,1000]" pageId="36" pageNumber="588">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
There is no specific information available for this species, but the White-tailed Olalla Rat is probably nocturnal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="588" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="36.[95,1305,302,1317]" pageId="36" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[98,809,1045,1078]" pageId="36" pageNumber="588">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
There is no information available for this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="588" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="36.[95,1305,302,1317]" pageId="36" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[98,449,1128,1157]" pageId="36" pageNumber="588">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. Additional ecological studies of the White-tailed Olalla Rat—a rare mountain endemic—are needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
